WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.041 --> 00:00:02.168
Did he lose the 2020 election?

00:00:02.168 --> 00:00:04.212
Tim, I'm focused on the future.

00:00:04.212 --> 00:00:07.257
Did Kamala Harris censor Americans
from speaking

00:00:07.257 --> 00:00:11.011
their mind
in the wake of the 2020 Covid situation?

00:00:11.052 --> 00:00:13.805
That is that is a damning non-answer.

00:00:13.805 --> 00:00:16.683
It's a damning non-answer
for you to not talk about censorship.

00:00:16.683 --> 00:00:19.686
Obviously, Donald Trump and I think that
there were problems in 2020.

00:00:19.728 --> 00:00:22.564
We've talked about it.
I'm happy to talk about it further.

00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:25.608
But you guys attack us for not believing

00:00:25.608 --> 00:00:28.737
in democracy, the most sacred
right under the United States.

00:00:28.737 --> 00:00:30.947
Democracy is the First Amendment.

00:00:30.947 --> 00:00:34.743
You yourself have said there's no
First Amendment right to misinformation.

00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:37.328
Kamala Harris wants to use

00:00:37.328 --> 00:00:40.957
government and big tech to silence people
from speaking their minds.

00:00:41.082 --> 00:00:44.252
That is a threat to democracy
that will long outlive this present

00:00:44.252 --> 00:00:45.045
political moment.

00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:48.757
I would like Democrats and Republicans
to both reject censorship.

00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:50.467
Let's persuade one another.

00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:53.845
Let's argue about ideas
and then let's come together afterwards.

00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:56.014
You can't yell fire in a crowded theater.

00:00:56.014 --> 00:00:58.266
That's that's the test.
That's the Supreme Court test.

00:00:58.266 --> 00:00:59.893
Tim, fire in a crowded theater.

00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:04.022
You guys wanted to kick people off of
Facebook for saying that toddlers shouldn’t wear masks.

00:01:04.355 --> 00:01:05.815
Senator, the governor does have the floor.

00:01:05.815 --> 00:01:07.776
That’s not fire in a crowded theater.

00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:10.695
That is criticizing
the policies of the government,

00:01:10.695 --> 00:01:12.614
which is the right
of every American.

00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:14.991
Senator, the governor does have the floor
for one minute to respond to you. Please.

00:01:14.991 --> 00:01:17.535
Yeah, but I don't run Facebook.

00:01:17.535 --> 00:01:21.790
What I do know is, is
I see a candidate out there who refused.

00:01:21.790 --> 00:01:24.375
And now again
and this I'm pretty shocked by this.

00:01:24.375 --> 00:01:27.087
He lost the election.
This is not a debate.

00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:30.882
If you become vice president,
why should Americans trust that

00:01:30.882 --> 00:01:34.511
you will give Donald Trump the advice
he needs to hear,

00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:37.722
and not just the advice he wants to hear? 

00:01:37.722 --> 00:01:38.473
Well, first of all, Margaret,

00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:40.558
because I've always been open
and sometimes, of course,

00:01:40.558 --> 00:01:43.228
I've disagreed with the president,
but I've also been extremely open

00:01:43.228 --> 00:01:45.772
about the fact
that I was wrong about Donald Trump.

00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:46.272
I was wrong,

00:01:46.272 --> 00:01:47.148
first of all, because

00:01:47.148 --> 00:01:50.360
I believed some of the media stories
that turned out to be dishonest

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:52.028
fabrications of his record.

00:01:52.028 --> 00:01:55.365
But most importantly, Donald Trump
delivered for the American people

00:01:55.573 --> 00:01:58.326
rising wages, rising take home pay,

00:01:58.326 --> 00:02:01.788
an economy that worked for normal
Americans, a secure southern border.

00:02:01.913 --> 00:02:04.874
A lot of things, frankly, that I didn't
think he'd be able to deliver on.

00:02:04.874 --> 00:02:07.210
And yeah, when you screw up,
when you misspeak,

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:09.295
when you get something wrong
and you change your mind,

00:02:09.295 --> 00:02:11.297
you ought to be honest
with the American people about it.

00:02:11.297 --> 00:02:14.467
You said you were in Hong Kong
during the deadly Tiananmen Square

00:02:14.467 --> 00:02:17.470
protests in the spring of 1989,

00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:20.849
but Minnesota Public Radio
and other media outlets are reporting that

00:02:20.849 --> 00:02:25.186
you actually didn't travel to Asia
until August of that year.

00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:29.065
Look, I will be the first to tell you
I have poured my heart into my community.

00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:32.193
I've tried to do the best I can,
but I've not been perfect.

00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:35.113
And I'm a knucklehead at times,
but it's always been about that.

00:02:35.113 --> 00:02:37.448
Many times I will talk a lot.

00:02:37.448 --> 00:02:39.784
I will get caught up in the rhetoric.

00:02:39.784 --> 00:02:43.621
But being there, the impact it made,
the difference it made in my life.

00:02:43.621 --> 00:02:46.249
I learned a lot about China.
I hear the critiques of this.

00:02:46.249 --> 00:02:48.334
I would make the case that Donald Trump

00:02:48.334 --> 00:02:50.086
should have come on
one of those trips with us.

00:02:50.086 --> 00:02:54.549
I guarantee you he wouldn't be,
praising Xi Jinping about Covid.

00:02:54.757 --> 00:02:58.136
And I guarantee you he wouldn't
start a trade war that he ends up losing.

00:02:58.261 --> 00:02:59.262
So first of all, Margaret,

00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:02.473
before we talk about deportations,
we have to stop the bleeding.

00:03:02.473 --> 00:03:06.686
We have a historic immigration crisis
because Kamala Harris started

00:03:06.853 --> 00:03:10.982
and said that she wanted to undo
all of Donald Trump's border policies.

00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:12.775
Kamala Harris was the attorney general

00:03:12.775 --> 00:03:15.069
of the largest state,
a border state in California.

00:03:15.069 --> 00:03:18.656
She's the only person in this race
who prosecuted transnational gangs

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:21.284
for human
trafficking and drug interventions.

00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:23.912
But look, we all want to solve the — I.

00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:25.872
Most of us want to solve this.

00:03:25.872 --> 00:03:30.835
That's why we had the fairest
and the toughest bill on immigration

00:03:31.002 --> 00:03:32.086
that this nation’s seen.

00:03:32.086 --> 00:03:35.089
But as soon as that was getting ready to pass
and actually tackle this,

00:03:35.131 --> 00:03:36.591
Donald Trump said no.

00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:40.428
He told them to vote against it
because it gives him a campaign issue.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:41.387
It gives him,

00:03:41.387 --> 00:03:44.515
what would Donald Trump talk about
if we actually did some of these things?

00:03:44.557 --> 00:03:48.519
The only thing that she did
when she became the vice president,

00:03:48.519 --> 00:03:53.107
when she became the appointed border
czar, was to undo 94

00:03:53.107 --> 00:03:56.277
Donald Trump executive actions
that opened the border.

00:03:56.402 --> 00:04:01.115
This problem is leading to massive
problems in the United States of America.

00:04:01.115 --> 00:04:05.119
We could come together and solve this
if we didn't let Donald Trump continue

00:04:05.119 --> 00:04:06.162
to make it an issue.

00:04:06.162 --> 00:04:09.874
And the consequences in Springfield were
the governor had to send

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.544
state law enforcement
to escort kindergartners to school.

00:04:13.962 --> 00:04:18.299
I believe Senator Vance wants to solve
this, but by standing with Donald Trump

00:04:18.508 --> 00:04:22.136
and not working together to find
a solution, it becomes a talking point.

00:04:22.178 --> 00:04:26.557
And when it becomes a talking point
like this, we dehumanize and villainize

00:04:26.683 --> 00:04:27.767
other human beings.

00:04:27.767 --> 00:04:30.645
Now, Governor Waltz
brought up the community of Springfield,

00:04:30.645 --> 00:04:34.691
and he's very worried about the things
that I've said in Springfield.

00:04:34.691 --> 00:04:38.903
Look, in Springfield, Ohio, and
in communities all across this country.

00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:41.114
You've got schools that are overwhelmed.

00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:43.074
You've got hospitals that are overwhelmed.

00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:45.785
You've got housing
that is totally unaffordable

00:04:45.785 --> 00:04:46.744
because we brought in

00:04:46.744 --> 00:04:50.873
millions of illegal immigrants to compete
with Americans for scarce homes.

00:04:50.873 --> 00:04:52.208
The people that I'm most worried

00:04:52.208 --> 00:04:55.253
about in Springfield,
Ohio, are the American citizens

00:04:55.378 --> 00:04:58.840
who have had their lives
destroyed by Kamala Harris's open border.

00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:00.633
It is a disgrace to him.

00:05:00.633 --> 00:05:02.343
And I actually think I agree with you.

00:05:02.343 --> 00:05:05.722
I think you want to solve this problem,
but I don't think that Kamala Harris does.

00:05:05.763 --> 00:05:09.851
I don't talk about my faith a lot,
but Matthew 25:40 talks

00:05:09.851 --> 00:05:12.312
about to the least amongst us,
you do unto me.

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:14.731
I think that's true of most Americans.

00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:16.899
They simply want order to it.

00:05:16.899 --> 00:05:18.192
This bill does it.

00:05:18.192 --> 00:05:20.778
It's funded.
It's supported by the people who do it.

00:05:20.778 --> 00:05:24.532
And it lets us keep our dignity
about how we treat other people.

00:05:24.615 --> 00:05:27.869
Just to clarify, for our viewers,
Springfield, Ohio,

00:05:27.869 --> 00:05:30.872
does have a large number
of Haitian migrants

00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:34.208
who have legal status
or temporary protected.

00:05:34.417 --> 00:05:35.626
Well., Margaret —

00:05:35.626 --> 00:05:38.004
But thank you, Senator.
We have so much to get to.

00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:39.005
I think it's important.

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:41.174
But I turn now to the economy. 

00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:44.469
The rules were that you got a fact check,
and since you're fact

00:05:44.469 --> 00:05:47.597
checking me, I think it's important to say
what's actually going on.

00:05:47.889 --> 00:05:50.099
So there's an application called the CBP.

00:05:50.099 --> 00:05:54.312
One app where you can go on
as an illegal migrant, apply for asylum

00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:58.066
or apply for parole
and be granted legal status

00:05:58.316 --> 00:06:02.153
at the wave of a Kamala
Harris open border wand.

00:06:02.403 --> 00:06:05.114
That is not a person coming in
applying for a green card

00:06:05.114 --> 00:06:06.407
and waiting for ten years.

00:06:06.407 --> 00:06:07.408
Thank you, Senator.

00:06:07.408 --> 00:06:09.911
That is the faciliatation of illegal immigration. Margaret.

00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.914
Thank you, Senator,
for describing the legal process.

00:06:13.289 --> 00:06:15.708
And Kamala Harris opened up that pathway.

00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:16.709
Thank you, Senator.

00:06:16.709 --> 00:06:18.419
Those laws have been on the books since 1990.

00:06:18.419 --> 00:06:19.837
Thank you gentlemen. This

00:06:20.838 --> 00:06:23.174
has not been on the books since 1990.

00:06:23.174 --> 00:06:25.426
It's something that was created.

00:06:25.426 --> 00:06:29.263
Gentlemen, the audience can't hear you
because your mics are cut.

00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:31.641
You know,
I grew up in a working class family

00:06:31.641 --> 00:06:33.559
in a neighborhood
where I knew a lot of young women

00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:37.146
who had unplanned pregnancies
and decided to terminate those pregnancies

00:06:37.438 --> 00:06:39.607
because they feel like
they didn't have any other options.

00:06:39.607 --> 00:06:41.317
One of them is actually very dear to me.

00:06:41.317 --> 00:06:42.610
She felt like if she hadn't

00:06:42.610 --> 00:06:45.196
had that abortion,
that it would have destroyed her life

00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:47.615
because she was in an abusive
relationship.

00:06:47.615 --> 00:06:51.160
And I think that what I take from
that as a Republican who proudly wants

00:06:51.160 --> 00:06:55.123
to protect innocent life in this country,
who proudly wants to protect

00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:56.916
the vulnerable, is that my party,

00:06:56.916 --> 00:07:01.587
we've got to do so much better of a job
at earning the American people's

00:07:01.587 --> 00:07:05.216
trust back on this issue,
where they, frankly, just don't trust us.

00:07:05.258 --> 00:07:08.594
And I think that's one of the things that
Donald Trump and I are endeavoring to do.

00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:12.306
I want us as a Republican Party
to be pro-family

00:07:12.306 --> 00:07:14.016
in the fullest sense of the word.

00:07:14.016 --> 00:07:15.935
I want us to support fertility treatments.

00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:19.147
I want us to make it easier for moms
to afford to have babies.

00:07:19.188 --> 00:07:22.233
I want to make it easier
for young families to afford a home

00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:24.735
so they can afford a place
to raise that family.

00:07:24.735 --> 00:07:27.947
And I think there's so much that we can do
on the public policy

00:07:27.947 --> 00:07:30.950
front just to give women more options.

00:07:31.033 --> 00:07:34.078
When you listen to Vice President Harris
talk about this subject, can you hear me

00:07:34.078 --> 00:07:34.996
talk about it?

00:07:34.996 --> 00:07:36.998
You hear us talking exactly the same.

00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:40.668
Donald Trump is trying to figure out
how to get the political right of this.

00:07:40.751 --> 00:07:43.546
I agree with a lot of what
Senator Vance said about what's happening.

00:07:43.546 --> 00:07:45.256
His running mate, though, does not.

00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:47.675
And that's the problem.
I got a 17-year-old and

00:07:48.759 --> 00:07:51.971
and he witnessed a shooting
at a community center playing volleyball.

00:07:51.971 --> 00:07:53.264
Those things don't leave you.

00:07:53.264 --> 00:07:56.350
No one's trying to scare monger
and say, we're taking your guns, but

00:07:56.350 --> 00:08:01.063
I ask all of you out there, do you want
your schools hardened to look like a fort?

00:08:01.606 --> 00:08:05.526
Is that is that what we have to go
when we know there's countries

00:08:05.526 --> 00:08:09.489
around the world that their children
aren't practicing these types of drills?

00:08:09.864 --> 00:08:10.865
They're being kids.

00:08:10.865 --> 00:08:13.034
We owe it to them to get a fix.

00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:13.659
Tim, first of all,

00:08:13.659 --> 00:08:15.786
I didn't know that your 17 year old
witnessed the shooting,

00:08:15.786 --> 00:08:17.997
and I'm sorry about that,
and I appreciate it.

00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:20.625
Christ have mercy. It is. It is awful.

00:08:20.625 --> 00:08:24.086
We unfortunately have a mental health
crisis in this country that I really do

00:08:24.086 --> 00:08:25.129
think that we need to get

00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:26.964
to the root causes of,
because I don't think it's

00:08:26.964 --> 00:08:29.800
the whole reason why
we have such a bad gun violence problem.

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:31.302
But I do think it's a big piece of it.

00:08:31.302 --> 00:08:34.305
Just because you have a mental health
issue doesn't mean you're violent.

00:08:34.388 --> 00:08:37.433
And I think what we end up doing
is we start looking for a scapegoat.

00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:39.894
Sometimes it just is the guns.

00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:41.979
Governor, you say trust the experts.

00:08:41.979 --> 00:08:46.150
But those same experts for 40 years said
that if we shipped our manufacturing base

00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:48.069
off to China, we'd get cheaper goods.

00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.195
They lied about that.

00:08:49.195 --> 00:08:51.531
They said if we cheap
shipped our industrial base off

00:08:51.531 --> 00:08:53.658
to other countries,
to Mexico and elsewhere,

00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:55.368
it would make the middle class stronger.

00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.078
They were wrong about that.

00:08:57.078 --> 00:09:00.998
They were wrong about the idea
that if we made America less self-reliant,

00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:05.503
less productive in our own nation,
that it would somehow make us better off.

00:09:05.628 --> 00:09:07.004
And they were wrong about it.

00:09:07.004 --> 00:09:10.925
And for the first time in a generation,
Donald Trump had the wisdom

00:09:11.050 --> 00:09:15.763
and the courage to say to that bipartisan
consensus, we're not doing it anymore.

00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:19.141
Much of what the senator said right
there, I'm in agreement with him on this.

00:09:19.225 --> 00:09:22.687
I watched it happen to I watched it to
my communities, and we talked about that.

00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:25.064
We're in agreement
that we bring those home.

00:09:25.064 --> 00:09:27.066
The issue is Donald
Trump is talking about it.

00:09:27.066 --> 00:09:30.653
Kamala Harris has a record 250,000
more manufacturing jobs

00:09:30.778 --> 00:09:32.196
just getting out of the IRA.

00:09:32.196 --> 00:09:33.948
But may respond to that. Yes.

00:09:33.948 --> 00:09:35.533
So so appreciate that.

00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:39.579
So if you notice what Governor Waltz
just did, as he said, first of all, Donald

00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:41.289
Trump has to listen to the experts.

00:09:41.289 --> 00:09:43.124
And then when he acknowledges
the experts screwed up,

00:09:43.124 --> 00:09:46.127
he said, well, Donald Trump
didn't do nearly as good of a job as this.

00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:48.045
No, that's a generalization.

00:09:48.045 --> 00:09:50.673
So what Tim Walz is doing
and I honestly, Tim,

00:09:50.673 --> 00:09:53.718
I think he got a tough job here
because you've got to play whack a mole.

00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:54.635
You've got to pretend

00:09:54.635 --> 00:09:58.306
that Donald Trump didn't deliver rising
take home pay, which of course he did.

00:09:58.472 --> 00:10:02.059
You've got to pretend that Donald Trump
didn't deliver lower inflation, which

00:10:02.101 --> 00:10:03.060
of course he did.

00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:04.270
And then you simultaneously

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:07.481
got to defend Kamala Harris's
atrocious economic record,

00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:12.028
which has made gas, groceries and housing
unaffordable for American citizens.

